{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppBackend\/runMainLoop(_:)"},"abstract":[{"text":"Often in UI frameworks (such as Gtk), code is run in a callback","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"after starting the app, and hence this generic root window creation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"API must reflect that. This is always the first method to be called","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and is where boilerplate app setup should happen.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"runMainLoop"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"callback"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"@escaping"},{"kind":"text","text":" @"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" () -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Void"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Runs the backend’s main run loop. The app will exit when this method"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"returns. This wall always be the first method called by SwiftCrossUI."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The callback is where SwiftCrossUI will create windows, render","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"initial views, start state handlers, etc. The setup action must be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"run exactly once. The backend must be fully functional before the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"callback is ready.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is up to the backend to decide whether the callback runs before or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"after the main loop starts. For example, some backends such as the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AppKit"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"backend can create windows and widgets before the run loop starts, so it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"makes the most sense to run the setup before the main run loop starts (it’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"also not possible to run the setup function once the main run loop starts"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"anyway). On the other side is the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk"},{"type":"text","text":" backend which must be on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"main loop to create windows and widgets (because otherwise the root"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"window has not yet been created, which is essential in Gtk), so the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"setup function is passed to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk"},{"type":"text","text":" as a callback to run once the main"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"run loop starts."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/appbackend\/runmainloop(_:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI","doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppBackend"]]},"metadata":{"required":true,"title":"runMainLoop(_:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"SwiftCrossUI"}],"remoteSource":{"fileName":"AppBackend.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/stackotter\/swift-cross-ui\/blob\/main\/Sources\/SwiftCrossUI\/Backend\/AppBackend.swift#L123"},"externalID":"s:12SwiftCrossUI10AppBackendP11runMainLoopyyyyScMYccF","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"runMainLoop","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Void","preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://SwiftCrossUI/documentation/SwiftCrossUI":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI","url":"\/documentation\/swiftcrossui","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create cross-platform desktop apps for macOS, Linux, Windows, iOS and tvOS."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"collection","title":"SwiftCrossUI"},"doc://SwiftCrossUI/documentation/SwiftCrossUI/AppBackend/runMainLoop(_:)":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"runMainLoop","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Void","preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppBackend\/runMainLoop(_:)","title":"runMainLoop(_:)","required":true,"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/appbackend\/runmainloop(_:)","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Often in UI frameworks (such as Gtk), code is run in a callback","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"after starting the app, and hence this generic root window creation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"API must reflect that. This is always the first method to be called","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and is where boilerplate app setup should happen.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SwiftCrossUI/documentation/SwiftCrossUI/AppBackend":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftcrossui\/appbackend","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A backend that can be used to run an app. Usually built on top of an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"existing UI framework."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftCrossUI\/documentation\/SwiftCrossUI\/AppBackend","title":"AppBackend","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"AppBackend"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"AppBackend"}]}}}